<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include("./partials/head.ejs") %>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #555;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include("./partials/navbar.ejs") %>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Authentication Data Protection</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, monitor, analyze, or track authentication data. Authentication details include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Username</li>
                <li>Password</li>
                <li>Email</li>
                <li>Full Name</li>
                <li>Avatar</li>
                <li>Cover Image</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Data Collection & Usage</h2>
            <p>Any data not explicitly listed above is not considered private or subject to protection under this
                policy. This includes, but is not limited to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Articles</li>
                <li>User interactions within the platform</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Such data may be monitored, analyzed, sold, or tracked in the present or in the future.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Publicly Visible Information & User Caution</h2>
            <p>Since author names and avatars are publicly visible, we strongly advise users to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Avoid using real names or usernames that resemble their real identity.</li>
                <li>Use avatars that do not contain identifiable personal information.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Public visibility means that individuals who disagree with your views may attempt to retaliate in real
                life. Protecting your privacy is your responsibility.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Disclaimer</h2>
            <p>We are not liable for the public exposure of authentication data such as avatars and full names, as they
                are explicitly displayed on the platform.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%- include("./partials/footer.ejs") %>
</body>

</html>